headline: ‘Casino-Like’ Market Powers Robinhood to 450% Gain in Trump Era
summary: Shares of the platform — used to trade stocks, cryptocurrencies and other assets — have soared around 450% since Trump’s win last November, making it the biggest gainer among companies that were worth at least $10 billion ahead of the 2024 election, data compiled by Bloomberg show.  A number of Trump administration policies have helped fuel that surge, including the president’s full-throated support of the cryptocurrency industry and a global trade war that has drawn investors hoping to profit from swings in broader markets.

headline: Robinhood crypto revenue falls short, announces CFO transition
summary: Robinhood (HOOD) posted third quarter earnings of $0.61 per share. Net revenue was $1.27 billion versus a $1.21 billion estimate. Average revenue per user was $191. The expectation was for $182. Crypto revenues fell short, $268 million compared to an expected $287.2 million. The company also announced CFO Jason Warnick will retire, with Shiv Verma replacing him.
